---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'axa-global', text: 'AXA Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'asia-considerations', text: 'Asia-Pacific Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'AXA Global Review', href: '/providers/axa-global' },
  { title: 'Thailand Insurance', href: '/countries/thailand/insurance' },
  { title: 'Singapore Expat Guide', href: '/insurance-for/expats' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Asia Network', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Excellent', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', cigna: 'Unlimited', bupa: 'Unlimited', axa: '€3M' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing', cigna: 'Extensive', bupa: 'Extensive', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Hong Kong Expertise', cigna: 'Strong', bupa: 'Very Strong', axa: 'Strong' },
  { feature: 'Singapore Network', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Excellent', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Thailand Network', cigna: 'Very Good', bupa: 'Very Good', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'App Quality', cigna: 'Best', bupa: 'Good', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'Overall choice', bupa: 'HK & Singapore', axa: 'Value seekers' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 35', cigna: '$280-450/mo', bupa: '$300-500/mo', axa: '$220-350/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', cigna: '$400-600/mo', bupa: '$450-650/mo', axa: '$320-480/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 40', cigna: '$650-950/mo', bupa: '$700-1,000/mo', axa: '$520-780/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', cigna: '$900-1,400/mo', bupa: '$950-1,500/mo', axa: '$750-1,100/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs AXA: Best Insurance for Asia-Pacific Expats 2026"
  description="Compare the top 3 insurers for expats in Asia: Cigna Global, Bupa Global, and AXA Global. Coverage, networks, and pricing for Singapore, Hong Kong, Thailand, and more."
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs AXA: Asia-Pacific Expat Insurance Compared"
  subheadline="The three leading premium insurers for Asia-Pacific. All excellent—but each has regional strengths. Here's how to choose."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Overall</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best app, fastest claims, excellent network across all of Asia. The safest choice for most expats.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best for HK/Singapore</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Deepest roots in Hong Kong and Singapore. Excellent direct billing at premium hospitals.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">AXA Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">10-15% cheaper than Cigna/Bupa with solid coverage. Good choice for cost-conscious expats.</p>
      <a href="/go/axa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get AXA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Asia-Pacific expats have three premium options that dominate the market. Cigna and Bupa are neck-and-neck on coverage and network, with Cigna winning on digital experience and Bupa stronger in Hong Kong/Singapore specifically. AXA offers similar coverage at lower prices but with a slightly smaller network.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best App</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Fastest Claims</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Global Leader</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global is the safe choice for Asia-Pacific. Strong networks across every major market, industry-leading digital experience, and fast claims processing. If you're not sure which to pick, Cigna won't disappoint anywhere in the region.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Best mobile app and digital experience</li>
    <li>Fastest claims processing</li>
    <li>Excellent networks in Singapore, Hong Kong, Thailand, Japan</li>
    <li>24/7 English support</li>
    <li>Unlimited annual coverage</li>
    <li>Strong employer group business (continuity if changing jobs)</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Premium pricing (top of market)</li>
    <li>Some hospitals prefer Bupa in HK/Singapore</li>
    <li>Pre-existing condition exclusions can be strict</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Expats who want the best digital experience and fastest service. Those moving between multiple Asian countries. Corporate transferees.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">HK Specialist</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Singapore Strong</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Premium Service</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global has the deepest roots in Hong Kong and Singapore—markets where it's been operating for decades. Premium hospitals in these cities often have better direct billing relationships with Bupa. If you're settling in one of these financial hubs, Bupa may be the better choice.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strongest presence in Hong Kong and Singapore</li>
    <li>Best direct billing at premium hospitals</li>
    <li>Excellent customer service</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
    <li>Good pre-existing condition handling</li>
    <li>Strong local support teams</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>App not as polished as Cigna</li>
    <li>Claims processing slightly slower</li>
    <li>Less competitive in mainland China</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Long-term expats in Hong Kong or Singapore. Those who prioritize direct billing at top hospitals. Families who want premium service.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="axa-global">AXA Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Strong Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">French Insurer</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    AXA Global offers premium-tier coverage at 10-15% less than Cigna and Bupa. The network is slightly smaller, but still excellent for most expats. A smart choice for those who want comprehensive coverage without paying top-of-market prices.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>10-15% cheaper than Cigna/Bupa</li>
    <li>Strong coverage across Asia</li>
    <li>Good mental health benefits</li>
    <li>Backed by major French insurer</li>
    <li>Competitive for families</li>
    <li>Good claims experience</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Smaller direct billing network</li>
    <li>€3M coverage limit (vs unlimited)</li>
    <li>Less brand recognition in Asia</li>
    <li>App and digital lagging Cigna</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Cost-conscious expats who still want premium coverage. Those in Thailand, Indonesia, or Philippines where all networks are similar. Families looking for value.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/axa-global" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get AXA Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/axa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare All Three"
    description="Get personalized quotes from Cigna, Bupa, and AXA based on your specific needs in Asia-Pacific."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Bupa tends to be the most expensive, followed closely by Cigna, with AXA offering meaningful savings. For families, the difference can be $200-400/month—significant over a year.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for comprehensive plans covering Asia including Singapore/Hong Kong. Actual prices vary based on age, health history, and selected benefits.
  </p>

  <h2 id="asia-considerations">Asia-Pacific Specific Considerations</h2>

  <h3>Healthcare Costs by Market</h3>
  <p>
    Asia's healthcare costs vary dramatically. Singapore and Hong Kong are among the world's most expensive—make sure your coverage limits match. Thailand, Malaysia, and Indonesia are more affordable but quality varies.
  </p>

  <h3>Singapore</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Excellent network, all major hospitals covered</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Best direct billing at Mount Elizabeth, Gleneagles, Raffles</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Good coverage, may need to claim reimbursement more often</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Hong Kong</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Strong presence, good at all major private hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Deepest roots, best relationships with HK Sanatorium, Matilda</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Solid but smaller direct billing network</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Thailand</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Excellent at Bumrungrad, Bangkok Hospital</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Good coverage, slightly fewer partnerships</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Good coverage at major Bangkok hospitals</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Japan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Best foreign insurer network in Japan</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Good but smaller Japanese network</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Limited direct billing, more reimbursement-based</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Move between multiple Asian countries</li>
        <li>Value the best digital experience</li>
        <li>Want fastest claims processing</li>
        <li>Are on a corporate plan or may switch employers</li>
        <li>Plan to spend time in Japan</li>
        <li>Prioritize convenience over cost</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are settling long-term in Hong Kong or Singapore</li>
        <li>Want the best direct billing at premium hospitals</li>
        <li>Value local support teams</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions needing coverage</li>
        <li>Prioritize service over savings</li>
        <li>Want lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose AXA Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want premium coverage at better prices</li>
        <li>Live in Thailand, Malaysia, or Indonesia</li>
        <li>Are comfortable with some reimbursement claims</li>
        <li>Have a family and want to manage costs</li>
        <li>Don't need top-tier direct billing everywhere</li>
        <li>€3M coverage limit is sufficient</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Which insurer has the best network in Asia?</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna and Bupa are nearly tied overall, with Bupa slightly stronger in Hong Kong/Singapore and Cigna slightly stronger in Japan. AXA's network is good but smaller. For most expats, any of these will cover your needs.
  </p>

  <h3>Is unlimited coverage necessary in Asia?</h3>
  <p>
    In Singapore and Hong Kong, yes—a major surgery or cancer treatment can exceed €3M. In Thailand or Malaysia, AXA's €3M limit is usually sufficient. Consider where you'll get treatment in a serious scenario.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use these in China?</h3>
  <p>
    All three work in China, but coverage and direct billing varies. Cigna tends to have the best mainland China network. For China-specific needs, also consider local options or China-focused international plans.
  </p>

  <h3>What about evacuation to Singapore for emergencies?</h3>
  <p>
    All three include medical evacuation. If you're in a country with limited healthcare, you'd be evacuated to the nearest appropriate facility—often Singapore for Southeast Asia. Check your specific plan's evacuation terms.
  </p>

  <h3>Which is best for families in Asia?</h3>
  <p>
    AXA offers the best value for families. Bupa has excellent maternity coverage in Singapore/Hong Kong. Cigna is the most flexible for families who move. All three are solid choices—it depends on your priorities.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices and coverage details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify current information directly with each provider before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
